I made a start on this model two or three months ago when it was announced on the list. It's available here........

http://guru2.karakasa.com/T_locomotive/download_e.html

Having made a start I had to put it aside for a while, but just got around to finishing it. Has anyone else got there?
It really is a fascinating model. A couple of still photos don't do it justice, I'll have to work out how to put a video film up on my site. When the model is gently pushed along, everything moves! The piston at the front moves back and forth along its runners, the connecting rods turn the flywheel on one side and a cogwheel on the other, which with the other three cogs turns the axles. (in fact, it works the other way around, but I can pretend).
I'm now thinking that there's some potential for a tiny electric motor in the boiler, to work the cogwheel which connects to the wheels.......

I'd warn that it's certainly not an easy build. I have a bit of a problem with some warped wheels, which could have been avoided with more care!

Roger
